        "annotationType": "ANNOTATION",
        "comment": {
          "commentType": "FUNCTION",
          "texts": [
            {
              "value": "Plays an important role in stimulating the translation of viral mRNAs. These mRNAs are capped but not polyadenylated, instead terminating in a conserved sequence 'GACC' at the 3' that is recognized by NSP3, which competes with host PABPC1 for EIF4G1 binding. The interaction between NSP3 and host EIF4G1 stabilizes the EIF4E-EIF4G1 interaction, thereby facilitating the initiation of capped mRNA translation"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
